[Comment "short-sweet-the-kings-indian-attack/course/27065, variation/4598793"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d3 Nf6 4. g3 d5 5. exd5 {This is my personal favourite. I 
prefer to keep my Knight on b1 to stay more flexible. We will take on d5 sooner 
or later and I like to do it on the first possible occasion.} Nxd5 6. Bg2 e5 
{Black tries to play the reversed Classical KID setup. I will show you the line 
that I use with Black, but here, we will enjoy having a tempo more.} 7. O-O Be7 
8. Re1 f6 9. c3 $1 {[%cal Bd3d4] This is the line that I've mentioned. I have 
great success with it in the KID. White plans to play d3-d4.} Be6 $6 {This is 
inaccurate, and it allows White to strike at once.} 10. d4 $1 cxd4 11. Nxd4 $14 
{[%cal Re5d4,Ge1e6] Whenever White manages to liquidate the centre, he will be 
better because our g2-Bishop is a monster and Black's position has been weakened 
by ...f6.} *

[Event "Short & Sweet: The King's Indian Attack"]
[Site "Main Level"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
